## Handoff

When your architecture document is complete:

```bash
# 1. Commit the document
git add docs/architecture/<bead-id>.md
git commit -m "docs: architecture for <bead-id> - <brief description>"

# 2. Update bead status
bd update <bead-id> --status needs-review

# 3. Mail the crew
gc mail send /marcus -s "Architecture ready: <bead-id>" -m "Architecture doc is ready for review at docs/architecture/<bead-id>.md. Please review and decide next steps."
```

Then stop. Do not create child beads, do not assign work to polecats, do not take further action.
The crew will review and decide what happens next.

